title: Pro-Life Group Targets Tech Giant Canva | 10 News+
description: Australian start-up success story Canva has drawn the ire of a pro-life organisation. After Roe v Wade was overturned in 2022 in the US, Canva promised to cover the cost of travel and accommodation for staff based in America if they had to travel to receive abortion care elsewhere. Right to Life have complained the design tool offers pro-choice templates but no pre-populated designs for pro-life causes with the group questioning if the tech company should be taking sides in the debate. title: Iran Protests Death Toll Passes 2,500 As Some Victims Are Identified | 10 News+
description: The death toll of mass protests in Iran has passed 2,500, with some human rights groups’ estimates placing it as high as 20,000. One of the identified victims is Rubina Aminian, a 23-year-old fashion student shot dead by security forces. There are also reports that public executions will start today, with many of those arrested and condemned to death being teenagers and university-aged youths. US President Donald Trump has told the protesters to “take over your institutions”, vowing that “help is on the way”. title: Trump Firm On Conquering Greenland Despite Tense US Meeting | 10 News
description: Denmark and Greenland’s foreign ministers say they have had a “frank” and “constructive” discussion with US officials regarding Greenland but failed to dissuade Washington’s desire to acquire the Danish territory.  Denmark's Foreign Minister Lars Lokke Rasmussen said the nation has committed additional funds for military capabilities and plans to form a working group to address the US’s security concerns.  US President Donald Trump has reiterated that Greenland and Denmark cannot be relied upon to protect the island if Russia or China wants to occupy the highly strategic – and mineral rich – territory.  “We didn't manage to change the American position. It's clear that the president has this wish of conquering over over Greenland. And we made it very, very clear that this is not in the interest of the kingdom," said Minister Rasmussen on Wednesday. title: Firefighters Rescue Goose Stuck On Lake | 10 News
description: Romanian firefighters have rescued a goose trapped on a frozen lake in Bucharest after ice formed around one of its legs.  A firefighter used a pickaxe and a small sled to reach the animal across the frozen surface before pulling it to safety.  The crew warmed and fed the goose inside their truck before releasing it back into the wild, officials said.  Temperatures in the capital plunged to -13°C overnight as Romania endured severe winter conditions.
